cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the use of automated decision support in a multi-agent system controlling an intelligent building to increase energy savings and customer value. This involves making bounded rational decisions under uncertainty and dynamic real-time constraints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) which deals with decision making, uncertainty, and optimization. The paper also involves multi-agent systems, which falls under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of monitoring and delegation of tasks to other agents falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves experimental findings related to tools for decision making, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with intelligent buildings, which falls under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
